<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005</DATELINE><TITLE>The evolving field of biodefence: therapeutic developments and diagnostics</TITLE><BODY>The threat of bioterrorism and the potential use of biological weapons against both military and civilian populations has become a major concern for governments around the world. For example, in 2001 anthrax-tainted letters resulted in several deaths, caused widespread public panic and exerted a heavy economic toll. If such a small-scale act of bioterrorism could have such a huge impact, then the effects of a large-scale attack would be catastrophic. This review covers recent progress in developing therapeutic countermeasures against, and diagnostics for, such agents.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>